drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: If at any point the city watch gets involved, lord and lady cassalanter become worried that someone has caught on to their plot. They replace all guards with a bearded devil disguised as a human.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Remember to replace Willifort Crowell's token with that of a tiefling. We placed his token in C1.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: If it is Founder's Day, the black viper is hiding in an alcove putting on her mask and hood in C2

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Lady Ammalia Cassalanter: Roll 1d100. 01-70, She's tending her butterfly garden in C25. 71-90, she's smoking on the balcony in C25a. 91-100 She's weeping before Osvaldo in the attic in area C24.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Lord Victoro Cassalanter: Roll 1d100. 01-70 He's in his office (area C6). 71-90 He's in the reading room (area C4). 91-100 he's with Ammalia at one of her three locations.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Terenzio and Elzerina Cassalanter: Roll 1d100. 01-50, they're playing in their room (area C18). 51-75 They're in the library (C3). 76-100 They're chasing butterflies in the garden (area C25).

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: The below three head servants are noted as cult fanatics but are in disguise as tiefling servants. Replace their tokens with the image of a tiefling.

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: On founders day several nobles and 100 of Waterdeep's poorest comoners gather on the lawn, ballroom, the entry, dining room and foyer

drawings.author: ZWZhNTMzZTE2NzI3
drawings.text: Four doppelgangers from the Yawning Portal have slipped into the party disguised as nobles. Their leader, Bonnie (see “Familiar Faces” journal entry), poses as a minor noblewoman going by the name Lymeria Lhaurilstar; she was hoping to have a fun night at the party, but she’s willing to help the characters if they need aid.  NOTE: REMEMBER TO CHANGE THE TOKEN PICTURE TO A NOBLE.
